    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen the system has gzipped manpages installed, :Man will not correctly match the section.\nThis is a problem when using a certain setup, like using gzipped manpages with mandoc, because some pages will not be accessible using :Man.\n\nThis happens because mandoc (incorrectly, probably) returns more results than expected. `man -w 3 strcpy` will also return 3p strcpy. Neovim does not handle the .gz extension correctly, and so the wrong page is displayed.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nEnsure you are using mandoc.\n\nEnsure you have gzipped manpages (default on Arch). You can check with `man -w strcpy`. If you don't have any:\n1. Download [Arch's man-pages](https://archlinux.org/packages/core/any/man-pages/download/) \n2. From the archive, copy /usr/share/man/man3/strcpy.3.gz and /usr/share/man/man3/strcpy.3p.gz to the appropriate locations on your computer, and make sure the existing versions of strcpy.3 are removed.\n\nThen,\n1. `nvim --clean`\n2. `:Man strcpy(3)`\n3. `:Man strcpy(3p)`\n4. You should see that Neovim displays the page from the wrong section.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhen specifying a section for :Man, Neovim should display the page from the correct section.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nmaster branch commit b47b0caba8586df57778f8cee07e5a9fa9ddb47c\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, Vim returns the correct page\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKitty 0.45.0-4\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nBuild from repo",
